.TH ir2mlod 1 "February 2026" "arma-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ir2mlod \- export visual-upgrade IR to Arma MLOD
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ir2mlod
.I ir_dir
.B -o
.I out.p3d
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ir2mlod
writes an editable MLOD from IR focused on visual LOD roundtrip workflows.
The default mode tolerates missing UV/material channels and emits placeholders.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -o , " --output " \fIpath\fR
Output MLOD path.
.TP
.B --mode \fIstrict|visual-upgrade\fR
Validation/export mode. Default is
.BR visual-upgrade .
.TP
.B --recompute-normals \fInever|if_missing|always\fR
Normal handling policy. Default is
.BR if_missing .
.TP
.B --deterministic
Use deterministic ordering for emitted selections.
.TP
.B --report \fIpath\fR
Write JSON diagnostics report.
.TP
.B --lod-only \fIcsv\fR
Export only specified LODs (for example
.BR 0.000,1.000,shadow ).
.TP
.B --autofix-selections
In visual-upgrade mode, drop out-of-range selection indices.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns non-zero on schema or validation failures.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mlod2ir (1),
.BR p3d_info (1)
